org.nerd4j.csv

Interface CSVProcessOutcome<M>

  • Type Parameters:
    M - type of the data model representing the CSV record.

    public interface CSVProcessOutcome<M>
    Represents the outcome of a CSV operation performed by either CSVReader or CSVWriter.

    This interface provides the following elements:

    1. The execution context of the operation.
    2. Some callkbacks called after the operation occurs.
    Since:
    version 1.2.0 support has been added for Java 8 lambdas. There are two new methods called on operation success and operation error. // * There are three new methods called on operation success, operation error and // * after the operation regardless the result., 1.2.0
    Author:
    Nerd4j Team

    • Method Summary

      All Methods Instance Methods Abstract Methods Default Methods 
      Modifier and Type Method and Description
      default CSVProcessOutcome<M> error(Consumer<CSVProcessError> consumer)
      This method calls the provided FunctionalInterface if an error occurred during the operation and provides the error to be consumed.
      CSVProcessContext getCSVProcessContext()
      Returns the operation execution context.
      M getModel()
      Returns the data model corresponding to the CSV record processed.
      default CSVProcessOutcome<M> success(Consumer<M> consumer)
      This method calls the provided FunctionalInterface if the operation has been successful and provides the data model to be consumed.
      default CSVProcessOutcome<M> then(Consumer<CSVProcessContext> consumer)
      This method calls the provided FunctionalInterface after the operation has been executed regardless the result and provides the related process context to be consumed.

      • getCSVProcessContext

        CSVProcessContext getCSVProcessContext()
        Returns the operation execution context.

        This object contains some information about the progress of the operation.

        IMPORTANT for performance reasons there is only one instance of the execution context. So the internal values of this object may vary during execution.
